HEADWORD: Scratchback
<hw>Scratch"back`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A toy which
imitates the sound of tearing cloth, -- used by drawing it across the
back of unsuspecting persons.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

